rComments: Do not take a philosophy course with this guy. His lectures were ridiculously repetitive and no material was really talked about - very hard marker and no expectations given. The entire class failed the first assignment (0 or 1/5) and when asked to provide suggestions or help, he refused and continued to mark all semester without criteria.

I love philosophy, but this prof absolutely ruined it. Not only does he dress extremely unprofessionally (baggy hoodie and jeans, unshaven beard) but he avoids answering students' questions; he will begin going off on a completely different topic that had nothing to do with the question. Terrible at lecturing, I learned NOTHING in his class.

This teacher does not explain anything he wants in a paper, expects no one to do better than a 60%. Very bad at explaining assignments. If you have a choice, I would Not pick his class, That is Strongly recomended. First year teaching this course, You can tell.
